sp.p:

                          Section. 16
                       Saint Augustine in the second booke of Baptisme against the Donatists, c. 7. saith, Many things are not found in the writings of the Apostles, nor in those that followed them, neither in the Councels;

and yet because such things haue bene obserued, and holden by the Church, we beleeue that they come from them, and are taught and commanded by them.
